    "question": {
        "en": "15. DEPRESSED FACIAL AFFECT (1-7):\n\n1 = Facial expression and voice animated during interview.  No sign of depressed affect.\n\n2 = Mild suppression of affect.  Some loss of spontaneity.\n\n3 = Overall loss of spontaneity.  Looks unhappy during parts of the interview (e.g., sullen face, lowered eyes, lack of animation in face).  Is capable of smiling, however, and does not avoid eye contact when discussing non-threatening areas.\n\n5 = Moderate restriction of affect throughout most of the interview.  Has longer and frequent periods of looking distinctly unhappy.  Nothing seems to enliven him/her.\n\n7 = Severe restriction of affect.  Looks distinctly sad and withdrawn.  Minimal verbal interaction throughout the interview.  Cries or may appear tearful."
